Miss Me, But Let Me Go

When I come to the end of the road
And the sun has set for me,
I want no rites in a gloom filled room
Why cry for a soul set free!
Miss me a little, but not for long,
And not with your head bowed low.
Remember the love we once shared,
Miss me, but let me go!
For this a journey we all must take,
And each must go alone;
It's all a part of the master's plan
A step on the road to home.
When you are lonely and sick of heart
Go to the friends we know,
And bury your sorrows in doing good deeds,
Miss me, but let me go. 

Robyn Rancman

We are avid cyclists and enjoy the outdoors (camping, swimming, hiking, sailing, kayaking, skiing, etc.). data.post:
The City Victoria is a special magical place. The are mountains and oceans surrounding it. Parks and forests and deer, walking freely around( this one in Cordova Bay. 
Mount Baker (behind the American juan de fuca gulf islands in the  Usa), stands up like a sugar top, popping up when you are on the ferry, or here, in the evening, driving through the stunning farmlands from Saanich to Victoria. 
There are beaches surrounding Victoria, this one is accessible from Island view road, driving between the ferry â´ at Swartz Bay, to Victoria. 
And happens to be where sister Kath Murray and Ted live, not far from Michell farms. 
I the city, the fairytale parliament buildings light up the harbor area and look like a fairy tale. They are right beside the proud Empress Hotel that unfortunately has been 'restored' and lost its charm and old beauty. So no photos of that. 
A favorite place. Victoria. Saying goodbye to it tomorrow.

data.post: Ole grÃ¸n Ã¥bner sit atelier pÃ¥ sÃ¸ndag! Altid en god oplevelse:)

These tests are in preparation for my Danish citizenship exam, i am taking with all the other hopeful foreigners, on November 30, 2017. 
I have to get 34 out of 40 correct. 
To be honest, I have never been so unsure of whether I will pass or not. 
No. I will pass!!!

Why am I doing this? 
Because I feel like a Dane and want to be able to vote at the government elections in the country I have spent two- thirds of my life:). I have not been able to vote in canada while I live here. 

And also because it is now possible to become a danish citizen AND keep my Canadian citizenship. I have been here for forty-two years and have been waiting for this possibility. 

I must say that if I knew that I had to study so much to start getting even average results, that I would never have started. 

Now I have begun, have paid almost 400 dollars, used many hours studying, well, of course I will finish it. 

These are links to the tests that I have been taking daily. A company has made an online studying forum, and one of their products is these daily test, to drill us through the 178 page book.

data.post:
In support of mental illness. Maybe if people's heads weren't buried in the sand of ignorance and they took the time to understand, instead of judging and thinking it won't happen to them because they have the perfect family, life would be a little bit easier for people that do experience this!
This hits close to home for me, for family and friends who live under this shadow.
The days of 'it' not being talked about or being taboo should be over.
In the most difficult moments of life you realize who your true friends are, and the people who really appreciate you.
Unfortunately, most social media 'friends' aren't true friends. They will send you a "like" here and there, but in reality they do not take time to read your status if they see it's lengthy. More than half will stop reading right here, or have already scrolled on to the next post on their page.
I decided to post this message in support of all those who continue to battle with their mental illness.
Now, let's see who will have taken the time to read this lengthy post right through to the end.
If you have read everything so far, please "like" it so that I can put a thank you on your page.
More mental health awareness is urgently needed. Just because you can't see it, doesn't mean people aren't suffering.
Please, try to spare a little of your time with someone who may just want to talk (about anything). Talking can help us all to cope a little more, keeping things bottled up just makes it worse.
Most people will say, "if you need anything, don't hesitate to call me, I'll be there to help you" but will they?
I believe a select few of my friends will post this, to show their support for those who may be struggling.
You just have to copy and paste rather than sharing.
I'd like to know who will take a minute out of their day to read this all the way to the end and then copy and paste it to their page, will you? If so, please write "done" in the comments.

Do Not Stand At My Grave And Weep
By Mary Elizabeth Frye

Do not stand at my grave and weep
I am not there; I do not sleep.
I am a thousand winds that blow,
I am the diamond glints on snow,
I am the sun on ripened grain,
I am the gentle autumn rain.
When you awaken in the morning's hush
I am the swift uplifting rush
Of quiet birds in circled flight. 
I am the soft stars that shine at night. 
Do not stand at my grave and cry, 
I am not there; I did not die.

Source: https://www.familyfriendpoems.com/poem/do-not-stand-by-my-grave-and-weep-by-mary-elizabeth-frye

data.post:
Six years ago. Jette was dying. We took her to her favorite beach one last time. She could just barely get out of the car and got to the bench. Some of us went for a small walk. Some of us stayed with her. We all knew that this was her last time at the beach. The sun shone. The was so much beauty and so much love. 
Thanks to all you siblings, to all our partners, to all friends and family, close and far away, and to George who let us invade their home so we could care for her there. 
It was her best way to die. And we did it! 
Thank you.
Totally enjoying my maternity leave With Pippis pups. Happy new year!

These farms
 produce approximately 17 million mink skins every year. The largest mink producent country in the world. 

They will close all production of minks, probably for the coming many years.300 thousand people will be restricted, schools, public transportation will close. 

So sad for so many people. 
People who have worked to make the best mink in the world, and have done so for generations. 

So good that the danish government is taking this new situation very seriously. 
Whatever one thinks about minks- doesnât matter. There are so many people whose lives are drastically changed  by this.

#geordiemademedoit i have been thinking alot about my nephew Geordie Murray, who died last year in a hunting accident,and his dear brother Michael Murray. Inagine all those 30 birthdays those two brothers had. 
This is the first birthday without geordie. 

So close in days. I was never there for those  birthdays - that aunt in Denmark Living far away and dropping in at Kath Murray and Ted murray, Jenny Murray Coad Naomi Murray Bullock Krystal Allen Michael murray for a small stay  in the summer. 
I remember all your smiles and happyfaces. I remember your wonderful Way of saying  grace at the table. I remember dreadful and funny Red Neck jokes that Geordie would tell. His great dialect. His quirky smile. 
And for all of you I remember your kind happy hugs and amazing ways of finding happiness in whatever was going on. 
You are all built out of the same cloth. Woven by Kath and Ted. 
You have all so much love, light and happiness in you and surrounding you. 
I have always been deeply impressed with your family. 
How am I celebrating #Wwgd ? 
I am hugging. Patting and admiring my dog. And she is being the most happy mum dog ever, and t am enjoying all the little ones she is taking care of. 
And I gave money to a homeless woman yesterday. 
And I am thinking of all of you murrayâs that are deeply sad. Sending love and praying for you all.

external_context.name:
The message of Unity is the main inspiration for the creation of the Ensemble. Unity makes strength and it is needed for the road ahead. The blooming symbol to represent this message are the federal flowers from every state and territory of the United States of America. The flowers are embroidered into the cashmere coat on the hem line in an  pattern that rises organically on the sideâs seams. On the dress, the embroidery is placed on the silk organza neckline and arms. The body of the dress is constructed in silk wool cady.
The Delaware flower is positioned at the heart level of The First Lady, from there, all the other flowers branch out.
The pieces were made entirely in New York City. The Embroidery and Coat were crafted in the garment district and the dress was assembled at the inhouse studio. Each flower took approximately two-four hours to embroider. Careful placements and color selections were carefully studied for weeks. Inside of the coat, representing the lifelong calling and service of Dr. Biden as an educator is a hand embroidery on the lining with a quote from Founding Father Benjamin FranklinÂ 
âTell me and I forget. Teach me and I remember. Involve me and I learn.â
The materials used were existing available fabrics to minimize the impact on the environment #gabrielahearst

â¤ (anon) Not my photo or words, but definitely my sentiments  

WHERE IS THE LOVE?
Family not invited to Christmas.
Church members disassociate with other church members.
Community members gossiping about others.
Neighbors telling on neighbors.
Businesses doing good in their communities, feeding their families and trying their best, and getting reported.
Loyal hardworking and dedicated employees fired for personal choices.
Kids are being told they can't play with other kids.
Parents are unable to walk their 8-year-olds into dance practice or sit and watch them, while others do and don't even think twice about those who can't.
Some people are unable to attend work Christmas parties while their employees gather and say cheers.
Children are afraid to go to school because they may have to cough and they don't want to cough or they'll get sent home.
People are being denied entry to some grocery stores in our very own country.
People are being denied medical care for their choices.
People dying because they can't get necessary surgeries.
People dying alone.
Seniors are locked up tighter than criminals.
I don't recognize our world anymore.
In two years, I live in a country I don't even know.
Regardless of your choices (and honestly I don't care which one you made nor do I wish to hear your opinion either way because I really don't care either way).
What I do care about is HOW WE ARE TREATING ONE ANOTHER BASED ON THOSE CHOICES.
Think you're better than someone because you made a different choice?
Think again.
We are all humans sharing the exact same planet.
Not one of us is better than another.
But the superiority is so thick, I'm nauseous.
What I'm saying here is you don't have to be pro or anti-anything to use the logic that LOVE is lost.
It's time to see reality.....
THE FEAR IS THICK
THE GOSSIP IS THICK
THE ANGER IS THICK
AND THICKEST OF ALL 
IS THE HATRED
'In it together 
Was quickly replaced withâ¦
âTogether only if you made the right choiceâ
As the divide expands.
My only answer to bridging the gap is LOVE
Don't think love will get us out?
I'd love to know what will because so far the lack of love has dug us a trench so deep I wonder if we'll ever be able to jump over it.
How a needle and a virus showed the world and each human in it what was already inside of them all along.
Because true colors come out when people are squeezed.
And as the squeezing continues.
And so many people spew hatred.
At people they once said they loved unconditionally - that means without condition (I'll love you no matter what you do or say or choose - that's what real love is folks)
I ask the questions...
WILL YOU BE PROUD OF YOURSELF after this?
Will you walk away with integrity?
Knowing you were KIND regardless of medical status?
There are so many things I could list that I want.
But truthfully?
All I want for Christmas is LOVE.
